The paper deals with the construction and security evaluation of probabilistic fingerprint codes, which are commonly used in the field of cryptography and information theory. The paper specifically focuses on collusion-secure codes against up to three pirates, which falls under the category of secure multi-party computation and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
